cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.SOC

The paper discusses the use of social media metrics for research evaluation, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with the organization, management, and dissemination of digital information, including research publications. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) are also relevant as they deal with social media and its impact on society. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as it deals with the retrieval and analysis of information, including social media metrics. Finally, cs.SOC (Social Computing) is relevant as it deals with the intersection of social behavior and computing systems, including social media platforms.
